    <h4>Biography</h4>
    <div class='note'>
      <p>John W. Linville is the current Linux kernel maintainer for wireless local area networking.  John is employed by Red Hat, where his primary focus is wireless networking in the upstream kernel and the Fedora distribution.  When not completely overwhelmed by these roles, John enjoys his role relaxing at home as a husband and father of three young children.</p>
    </div>
  
  
  
  
  
    

  
