      <h4>Proposals for this user</h4>
      


  

  
    <table class='proposals' cellspacing='0'>
      
      
        
        
        

      <tr class='proposal_row' id='proposal_row_64'>
        <td rowspan='2' class='description'>
          <h3>
            <a href="../login" class="favorite favorite_64"><span>*</span></a>
            
              <a href="../proposals/64" class="title">Modern Configuration API for Wireless Networking</a>
            
            
          </h3>

          <div class="excerpt">
            The wireless extensions API is universally hated by wireless developers on both sides of the user/kernel divide.  Fortunately the cfg80211 API is maturing as a modern alternative.  What is needed is for drivers (both new and old) to adopt cfg80211 as their configuration mechanism so that the long wireless extensions nightmare can finally end.
          </div>
        </td>

        
        <td class='track block track-6'>
          <a href="../events/2009bofs/tracks/6">Networking</a>
        </td>
        

        
          <td class='date'>
            06/15/2009
          </td>
        
      </tr>
